pyUBC - a library to access services of the University of British Columbia

---

ABOUT:

This library provides easy access to the various websites of the University of British Columbia (UBC). The CWL authentication present on most sites is built in to this system, and it is easy to add support for new sites. Webpages are scraped where no api is available for data. 

This library currently supports the following services:
- SSC
- Vista

---

REQUIREMENTS:

This library has been tested on Ubuntu 10.10 and 11.04 using python2.6 and python2.7. It should work on other systems but has not been tested.

---

USAGE:

A bunch of scripts showing how to use the library can be found in the scripts folder. These should be run from the scripts folder.

