SSC Terms of Use (from UBC's website, May 15th 2011).

I agree that I will not use any device, software or routine to interfere or attempt to interfere with the proper working of the Site. 

I agree that I will not use any robot, spider, other automatic device, or manual process to impose an "unreasonable or disproportionately large load" on UBC's infrastructure. An "unreasonable or disproportionately large load" is one that prevents other members of the University community from gaining fair and equitable access to Student Systems (by which we mean the Student Service Centre (SSC)). 

I understand that any activities undertaken in breach of this agreement will be considered non-academic misconduct and may result in disciplinary action as outlined in the Student Discipline section of the UBC Calendar 

